nl.tno.sensorstorm.storm

Class SensorStormBolt

  • java.lang.Object
    • backtype.storm.topology.base.BaseComponent
      • backtype.storm.topology.base.BaseRichBolt
        • nl.tno.sensorstorm.storm.SensorStormBolt
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    backtype.storm.task.IBolt, backtype.storm.topology.IComponent, backtype.storm.topology.IRichBolt, Serializable

    public class SensorStormBolt
extends backtype.storm.topology.base.BaseRichBolt
    This is a generic Bolt for the SensorStorm library. There are several configurations of this bolt possible. There are different constructors different configurations. On top a SensorStormBolt you can run an Operation and optionally a Batcher. You can use this Bolt without a Batcher. In that case you can run a SingleParticleOperation on top of this Bolt. You can also put a Batcher on this bolt. In that case you have to run a ParticleBatchOperation on top of this Bolt. Additionally, you can choose to have one instance of the Operation (and possibly the Batcher), or you can have a separate Operation (and possible Batcher) for each value of a field in the Tuple (e.g. the sensor id). If you do this, you usually want to use a SensorStormFieldGrouping with the same field name on the Spout or Bolt before this Bolt.
